Capital Markets

Company Overview of HCI Equity Partners



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Daniel M. Dickinson J.D.Co-Founder, Managing Partner, and Director, HCI Equity PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Mr. Daniel M. Dickinson, also known as Dan, J.D. has been a Co-Founder and Managing Partner at HCI Equity Partners since 2001 and also serves as its Director. Mr. Dickinson oversees the origination, management and development of the firm's investments. Previously, he spent more than 14 years in the field of corporate mergers and acquisitions and as the Co-Head of Global Mergers and Acquisitions at Merrill Lynch & Co., Inc. His roles at Merrill Lynch also included leading ... the European Mergers and Acquisitions Group as the Head of European M&A and prior to that, the Global Manufacturing and Services Mergers and Acquisitions effort as the Head of Global Manufacturing and Services M&A. Prior to joining Merrill Lynch in 1993, he started his career as a Vice President in the Merger and Acquisition Group at the First Boston Corporation. Mr. Dickinson served as the Lead Advisor to Mannesmann in its hostile takeover by Vodafone. Most of Mr. Dickinson‘s career has been focused on advising manufacturing companies and working in the capital goods, industrial component, automotive, process control, specialty material and electrical equipment sectors. He has also been a Senior Strategic and Financial Advisor to many of the largest industrial concerns, including Caterpillar, Progressive Waste Solutions, General Motors and Siemens. Mr. Dickinson serves as the Chairman of the Board of Educational Resources/Sunburst Technologies. He is also the Chairman of The Brown Corporation of America and Heckethorn Manufacturing Company. Mr. Dickinson serves as a Director of Dynamic Systems Inc.; Qualitor, Inc.; Morton Welding Company; Quadel Consulting Corporation; and Power & Composite Technologies, Inc. Mr. Dickinson has been an Independent Director at Caterpillar Inc. since December 13, 2006. He serves as the Chairman of Board of Visitors at Duke University's Pratt School of Engineering at Duke University and previously served as the Vice Chairman. Mr. Dickinson is the President of the Board of Trustees of the Cove School and serves on Alumni Board of Directors of Duke University. He serves as a Director and Member of Board of Visitors of University of Chicago Law School and the Board of Directors of the Paralympic Foundation and US Olympic. He served as a Director of Progressive Waste Solutions Ltd., since 2005. Mr. Dickinson served as a Member of Progressive Waste Solutions of TX, Inc., (alternate name IESI Corporation)'s Board of Directors since May 2001. He served as an Independent Director of Mistras Group, Inc. since August 2008 to October 21, 2014. He spent the last 20 years in advising and working with industrial products and services companies. Mr. Dickinson holds a J.D. and an M.B.A. from The University of Chicago and B.S. in Mechanical Engineering and Materials Science, magna cum laude, from Duke University.Read Full Background




